node.text: It's time to fire up the grill and spill the tea for this week's episode of Mad Genius with F&W Culinary Director at Large @justinchapple. He teaches us how to make a delicious bowl that consists of sweet tea-marinated pork tenderloin accompanied with grilled pineapple slices and a bed of fluffy rice with a piquant cilantro-lime dressing for a little kick. Tap the link in bio to get the recipe!

node.text: This week F&W Culinary Director at Large @justinchapple  takes a cue from regional barbecue sauces to create three bold dressings to transform summer salads into hearty main dishes. Full of flavor and inspiration, Texas Barbecue Sauce Vinaigrette, Sweet and Tangy Mustard Dressing and Alabama-style White Barbecue Dressing will punch up any salad green on the plate. Find out how to add some 'cue to your greens through the link in bio.

node.text: In this episode of #FWCooks, @la_yoselin of @todoverde showcases crispy edges and tender interior of versatile jackfruit in a deliciously savory plant-based taco that tastes like carnitas. Seasoned with cumin, chile flakes, and salt and served with a tart, creamy avocado salsa these tacos are a satisfying vegetarian meal.  Tap the link in our bio for the recipe!

node.text: In this sunny take on tiramisu, ladyfingers soak up a bright strawberry, balsamic, and orange liqueur mixture and are layered with orange-zest flecked mascarpone that's fluffy like whipped cream. Tap the link in our bio for the recipe!

node.text:
This Caramelized Five-Onion Dip is a mix of five different alliums—shallots, scallions, and sweet, yellow, and red onions—that give the classic an upgrade with layers of flavor. Served with chips, toasted bread, or vegetables, it's perfect for that thing you were invited to this weekend. Tap the link in bio for the recipe. 
🧅: @justinchapple 📸: @protazio

node.text: Cool off with this Cold Crab Spaghetti from @toupsmeatery. Sweet fresh jumbo lump crabmeat is tossed with segments of juicy tangerine, a touch of Thai chile for heat and a flurry of mint, basil, and parsley. A garnish of trout roe makes this cool pasta dish POP! Tap the link in bio for the recipe. 📸: @ericwolfinger

node.text:
Crushed saltine crackers and Parmesan cheese give these Tomato Pie Bars a crispy, savory bottom crust. The rich, savory filling is enhanced with mildly spicy curry powder and chipotle chile. Tap the link in bio for this updated riff on tomato pie! 
🍅: @jbrothersmiller 📸: @linda.xiao

node.text: Silky and sweet-spicy, glazed carrots are the star of the show in this Hot Honey–Carrot Flatbreads with Basil Chermoula recipe. Veg out on the ricotta-smeared naan with a drizzle of bright basil chermoula from @suzycupps. Tap the link in bio for the recipe. 📸: @protazio

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Food & Wine on August 07, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text:
This Creamy Vegan Pasta Primavera is a recipe triumph. Silky smooth macadamia milk creates a creamy sauce that envelopes each strand of pasta. The panko and umami-rich nutrional yeast topping provides deep flavor and crunch for contrast. Tap the link in bio for this plant-powered masterpiece.
🍽️: @anntaylorpittman 📸: @jencausey

node.text:
A warm bowl of butter spiked with Cajun seasoning and a splash of Louisiana-style hot sauce makes a downright delicious dipping partner for every bite of this Seafood Boil with Cajun Seasoning. Summer is the perfect time for this ultimate mix of cooked shrimp, king crab legs, clams, spicy andouille sausage, and corn on the cob. Tap the link in bio to get your boil on! 
Recipe: Liz Mervosh 📸: @jencausey
